name: "Radioactive Thug" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description:
[Liner pen on notebook page with digital embellishments, color, and moshing...] What eventually did Robespierre in was the radioactive fertilizer he used on his garden in an attempt to make gigantic veggies. It worked, but the radiation proved to much for his constitution, and he eventually faded into radio waves... ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)

[P.S. - This is piece #4 of 4 in a cross-chain project all based on the original pen drawing of Robespierre from my notebook.]
